<br />

<p><sup id="footnote-1">1</sup> The NASA article denies this, but also says that in 1984, they decided that the low values (whch went back to the 70s) were "real." Whether humans or software decided to ignore anomalous data, it appears that data was ignored.</p>

<p><sup id="footnote-2">2 </sup> "Information Platforms as Dataspaces," by Jeff Hammerbacher (in <em><a href="http://oreilly.com/catalog/9780596157128/ id=qvhu title="Beautiful Data">Beautiful Data</a></em>)</p>

<p><sup id="footnote-3">3 </sup> "Information Platforms as Dataspaces," by Jeff Hammerbacher (in <em><a href="http://oreilly.com/catalog/9780596157128/ id=aod4 title="Beautiful Data">Beautiful Data</a></em>)</p>
