<p class="comment-head">
<span class="author" id="comment-2695165">Leo Irakliotis
</span> 
<a href="#comment-2695165" title="Permalink to this comment"><span class="date">[ 5 July 2010 08:22 PM]</span></a>
</p>
<p>
<p>As I keel reading and reading the article, the academic inside me keeps repeating the same question: do we (academics) do a good, or even adequate job, at educating future data scientists?  Should we consider creating data science programs?  What can we do to offer better more relevant education to individuals who may be pursuing or using data science?  And who can possibly advise us about the practical realities of data science?</p>
</p>
</div>
